A struct is defined using the following syntax:
struct StructureName {
  data_type member1;
  data_type member2;
};
- **StructureName**: The name of the struct.
- **member1, member2**: Members (variables) of the struct.
After defining a struct, objects are created, and members are accessed using the dot operator: structure_object.member.

